                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.20 Mission/9–145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-01T10:00:00+07:00"
                            >September 1, 1945—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 1—2:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1494. For the Secretary and the President. Last night Generalissimo Chiang
                    Kai-shek advised me that it is indicated that the United States will send a
                    military mission (the Generalissimo would rather call it a Military Advisory
                    Board) to China. He respectfully suggests that when such a mission or board is
                    created that General Wedemeyer be made Chief of the Mission or Board. He
                    earnestly desires the continuance of Wedemeyer’s services in China. He stated
                    that because of Wedemeyer’s understanding of the military situation in China and
                    his understanding of the Chinese people and Government, his services would be of
                    great value in continuing the splendid relations that now exist between the
                    United States and China.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hurley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
